    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-21T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-21T07:35:00-05:00" n="466"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.105A/12–2144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-21T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 21, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 22—10:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>944. I have received a letter from Schwarzkopf sent to me after full discussion
                    with him of the proposal contained in Department’s telegram No. 697 of November
                    29 that Schwarzkopf approach Iranian Government on the subject of his assuming
                    jurisdiction over the Iranian city police.</p>
                <p>Contrary to the information given to the state [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>]
                    Schwarzkopf has never been approached by the Iranian Government on this subject.
                    Schwarzkopf and I are definitely of the opinion that it is inadvisable that the
                    approach come from the American side.</p>
                <p>I am forwarding by dispatch a copy of Schwarzkopf’s letter and my own opinion in
                    regard to this subject.<note n="47" xml:id="d466fn47">Neither printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
